f=Engineering/mia/custom/design-tokens/SKILL.md · in=design-tokens **atlas bridge**: brand kit atlas (Brand Studio's visual definer) owns single source truth frontend's design tokens colors, type scale, spacing, radii, shadows, motion. mia translates kit tokens consumes, brand product never drift apart, kit change flows product through one traceable path instead scattered hardcoded values. · p=designers brand kit engineers hardcode hex values, two diverge first week "brand blue" app three slightly different blues, none matching kit. Tokens fix this: kit defines values once, tokens carry them code, brand refresh kit amendment propagates, hunt through stylesheets. · wu=Triggers: "design tokens," "brand colors app," "the doesn't match brand," "update theme," brand kit change atlas, any styling otherwise hardcode brand value. · st:/ Protocol=`atlas's BRAND KIT (source of truth — colors, type, spacing, motion, etc.) \· -> Translate to tokens (assets/token-schema.md): semantic names, not raw values \· (token: color.action.primary → kit's brand blue — NOT #1A73E8 sprinkled in components) \· -> Tokens are the ONLY styling source components read; raw hardcoded brand values are a finding \· -> Kit change → token update → propagates everywhere the token is used (one path)` · in=**The brand kit source truth.** atlas owns it; mia consumes it. mia invent brand values "adjust" them code value change kit conversation atlas, token update. bridge's direction: kit tokens UI, never improvised brand. **Semantic tokens, raw values.** Tokens name intent (`color.action.primary`, `space.section`, `type.heading.lg`), raw values, components reference tokens only. `#1A73E8` component finding it's brand value won't follow kit changes. **One change path.** brand refresh updates kit tokens consuming component, automatically. component holds copy brand value; that's drift tokens exist prevent (dev's stack-drift rule, brand edition). **Traceability ways.** token traces kit source; token change traces kit amendment caused it. "why button blue" answer (the kit), kit audit find everywhere value used. **Drift finding.** value isn't token hardcoded color, off-scale spacing, one-off font size flagged review (mia's dev's): either needs token (extend schema) it's off-brand (fix it). Agent-generated code especially tends hardcode; catch it. **Tokens theme-able.** token layer theming (light/dark, white-label business) lives one token set theme, component code. toongine binds business's brand deployment without touching components. · of=`## Design Tokens: [scope] \· Source: atlas brand kit [ref/version] \· Tokens: [semantic name → kit value — colors/type/space/radii/shadow/motion] \· Component usage: [tokens only ✓ \· hardcoded brand values found: none / list → findings] \· Themes: [default / dark / white-label — token sets]` · pr=**The brand kit source truth** kit tokens UI, never improvised brand code., **Semantic tokens, raw values** components reference intent; hex component finding., **One change path** kit refresh propagates through tokens; component holds copy., **Traceable ways** token kit amendment; "why blue" answer., **Drift finding** non-token values get flagged (agent code hardcodes; catch it)., **Tokens carry themes** light/dark/white-label toongine's per-business brand binding. · f=brand kit (early business) mia defines provisional tokens placeholder values, clearly labeled, flags atlas's kit pending source truth; token STRUCTURE right even before values final., Kit code disagree kit wins (it's source truth); reconcile toward flag drift happened., One-off value genuinely needed (not brand) it's local style, brand token; keep out token namespace brand layer stays clean. · b:with Other Skills=**atlas (Brand Studio)**: owns brand kit source truth bridges; token changes trace kit amendments. cross-department seam plan names., **ui-accessibility-standards** (sibling): consumes tokens consistent, accessible components., **frontend-performance** (sibling): token-driven theming shouldn't bloat bundle (one token layer, duplicated styles)., **pixel (Brand Studio)**: production visual assets align kit., **dev/stack-profile**: CSS/token tooling (Style Dictionary, CSS vars, etc.) named there; drift dev's finding-rule applied brand values.